<strong>Write about sleep and the impact it has on your life now or at any point in your life</strong>

Once a month, <strong>ChicagoNow, </strong>the platform that hosts my blog,  sponsors an event that challenges us to  blog on a topic provided at 9pm.  We have one hour to write and post a post on a topic....see above.

Hmmmm......

<strong>What the hell does sleep have to do with divorce?</strong>

Sleep is essential in everyone's life!  When you are sleep deprived, you can become a zombie.   Think new baby and how all those wakeful nights are hard. Fast forward 18 years and think when you are waiting up when until  same "baby" returns home from a night out.

Sleep deprivation is terrible. Nothing else matters when you are sleep deprived.  Not food, not sex...nothing except to get a good night sleep.

Since my blog, <strong>DivorceChicagoStyle,</strong>  is about divorce in the Cook County court system, and  is clearly a "high conflict" divorce [12 years and two 20+ trials....if this is not a high conflict divorce, tell me what is?****]  here is how sleep and divorce connect:

"High conflict' divorce which is what I have been dealing with for more than twelve years.... it requires lots of sleep;

Sleep helps me me to deal from the stress of the never ending litigation: every day after the trials,  I would take a nap.

Sleep helps me to regain my energy to get up each day and be grateful for what I have: health, family, friends.

A good night sleep is when I wake up refreshed and  the first thing I  do is to be thankful that I am not still married to the person that broke all our wedding vows to be <strong>faithful</strong> and true.

<strong>A good night sleep makes the world right!  </strong>

*****In case you have not figured this out: this journey is not my choice.  My X told me that he would destroy me in 2003 and enjoy doing same. Of course, he has not done that.  Some folks just do not want to move on.  I  try to find humor in all aspects of my life and  the good news is that every chapter in this saga could be a segment in a TV series.  TV agents: feel free to contact me.

<strong>Thank you for reading my blog! </strong>

<strong>Between posts I tweet at @DivorceChicagoS which shares info on divorce news nationwide.</strong>

