<strong>Saturday, August 8, 2015</strong>

<a href="http://www.secondsaturday.com"><strong>Second Saturday Divorce Workshops</strong> </a> are in their 25th year.  Conducted by either a financial, legal or mental health professional, they are designed to  be a resource for women going through a divorce. Held on the second Saturday of every month [clever name?].  They are held at various locations throughout Illinois, go to the website to find one near you.

This Saturday one is being held at the <a href="http://www.newberry.org">Newberry Library</a>, 8:30am to 1pm. Contact Stuart Kruse at 312-775-6000 for more information.

The <a href="http://thelilactree.org">Lilac Tree's </a>Events:

<strong>Thursday, August 13th, 6:30 - 8:30pm</strong>

Divorce Math Series: Children and the Money It Takes to Raise Them!
(*and what you and your spouse can expect to pay/need)

The USDA has estimated that the average cost of raising a child to age 18 is $245,340 ---and then there is College.  This workshop will analyze the financial contributions you and your spouse may expect to make for child support, medical and child care, private school, camp, activity fees and related expenses. It will also examine College, the FAFSA application and the contributions you, your child and your spouse may be expected to provide.

Reservations required and you may pay at the door - $30
Evanston Public Library, 1703 Orrington Avenue, Evanston, IL 60201
Parking at Church Street Self Park multi-story garage at 525 Church Street, northeast corner of Church Street and Chicago Avenue.

<strong>Thursday, August 27th, 6:30 - 8:30pm</strong>

Contemplating Should I Stay or Leave My Marriage? Why is it so Hard to Decide to Divorce? This workshop, part presentation and part discussion, will address some of the complicated issues women face when deciding to divorce such as finances, children, guilt, fear, emotions, etc.,

Reservations required and you may pay at the door - $30
Evanston Public Library, 1703 Orrington Avenue, Evanston, IL 60201
Parking at Church Street Self Park multi-story garage at 525 Church Street, northeast corner of Church Street and Chicago Avenue.

<strong>Sunday, September 6,  2015 3:15 PM</strong>
The Chicago Divorce Support Meetup Group Monthly Meetup

From the website: "This group is open to anybody, male or female, going through divorce, separation or through a challenging breakup in general.  People find it hard to make the first step to come to a meeting and often comment afterwards how they had wished they had attended months before.  We generally function as an open forum where people can vent their feelings and frustrations, ask questions of each other and generally share their commonalities.  You are not the only one who feels like this."

Go to meetup.com for more information

Note that there are many other divorce related Meetup groups, including "Chicago Divorce Toolkit," Chicago Women in their 30s Facing Separation or Divorce."  And the one I like best: "The Optimistic Divorcees--Chicago!"

I welcome notices of future divorce information events. Send details to divorcechicagostyle@gmail.com.

